'''''Galaxy of Fear: The Swarm''''' is the eighth book in the young readers ''[[Star Wars: Galaxy of Fear]]'' series.

==Publisher's summary==
''Uncle Hoole wants to study the S'krrr--a race of creatures that look like giant bugs. While Hoole works, Zak and Tash visit the S'krrr's huge garden--it's the most beautiful place they have ever seen. It's also full of very strange creatures. When a batlike shreev swoops down at Zak, he panics and accidentally kills it. Suddenly, the garden is overrun by big beetles. When Zak wakes up in the middle of the night covered with creepy crawly bugs, he's terrified. Did Zak upset the garden's delicate ecological balance by killing the shreev? Or is something far more sinister at work?''

==Plot summary==
[[Zak Arranda/Legends|Zak Arranda]] interferes with the [[Engine/Legends|engines]] on Uncle [[Mammon Hoole|Hoole's]] [[Starship/Legends|ship]] and they land on [[S'krrr]]. After landing on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]], the ship's engines shut down and they are forced to stay. Zak fears that the accidental [[Death/Legends|killing]] of a predatory [[Shreev|shreev bat]] has upset the delicate [[Ecologist/Legends|ecological]] balance of the S'krrr. But the sudden explosion in the native [[Drog|drog beetle]] population can be pinned on [[Vroon]], a [[S'krrr (species)|native S'krrr]] who fanatically worships the beetles as descendants of a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Insectoid/Legends|insectoid]] life on the planet. The Arrandas and Hoole escape the ravenous swarms of beetles while avoiding the scrutiny of a visiting [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial officer]], [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]].

==Continuity==
The cover art of the book depicted [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]] in the uniform of an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]], though he only had the [[Military rank/Legends|rank]] of [[Captain/Legends|captain]] in this novel. At one point in the text, he was erroneously referred to as [[General/Legends|General]] Thrawn.<ref name="TERC" />

